/coronavirus_149_i_casi_confermati_conte_i_contagi_possono_crescere_-249427098/|title=Coronavirus, quarto morto, \u00e8 un 84enne di Bergamo. Sette regioni coinvolte per 30 milioni di italiani|date=24 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref> The Ministry of Health announced that it had engaged 31 laboratories in Italy to carry out the analysis of swabs from suspected COVID-19 cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/coronavirus-il-ministero-della-salute-ha-aggiornato-la-circolare-con-le-nuove-disposizioni-analisi-in-31-laboratori_15196699-202002a.shtml|title=Coronavirus, il ministero della Salute ha aggiornato la circolare con le nuove disposizioni: analisi in 31 laboratori|website=Tgcom24|language=IT|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref> Minister [[Roberto Speranza]] appointed Walter Ricciardi, a member of [[World Health Organization]]'s executive committee and former president of [[Istituto Superiore di Sanit\u00e0|Italian National Institute of Health]], as a special adviser for relations between Italy and international health organisations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_speranza_nomina_walter_ricciardi_come_consigliere_e_alle_regioni_dice_no_a_scelte_unilaterali_-249447649/|title=Coronavirus, Speranza nomina Walter Ricciardi come consigliere e alle Regioni dice: \"No a scelte unilaterali\"|date=24 February 2020|website=la Repubblica}}</ref> Filming of ''[[Mission: Impossible 7]]'' starring [[Tom Cruise]] in [[Venice]] was halted.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/mission-impossible-vii-halts-production-in-italy-due-to-coronavirus-outbreak/|title='Mission: Impossible VII' Halts Production in Italy Due to Coronavirus Outbreak|date=2020-02-24|website=TheWrap|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nMajor companies such as [[IBM]], [[Enel]], [[Luxottica]], [[PwC]] and [[Vodafone]] continued to allow employees to work from home. [[Generali Tower]] in Milan and [[Palazzo Madama]] in Rome installed thermal scanners to measure temperatures of visitors and employees.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.finanza.com/Finanza/Notizie_Italia/Italia/notizia/Coronavirus_Italia_Enel_ricorre_allo_smart_working_General-516928|title=Coronavirus Italia: Enel ricorre allo smart working. Generali installa scanner tecnici per misurazione febbre |website=finanza.com|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/politica/coronavirus_senato_scanner_termici_scolaresche-5072334.html|title=Coronavirus, il Senato corre ai ripari: scanner termici agli ingressi e stop alle scolaresche|website=ilmessaggero.it|language=it|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref> [[FAO Headquarters|FAO headquarters]] in Rome conducted temperature checks on visitors entering the building.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://roma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/alla_fao_obbligatoria_la_misurazione_della_febbre_all_ingresso-249495069/|title=Alla Fao, obbligatoria la misurazione della febbre all'ingresso|date=2020-02-24|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nMultiple regions in Italy such as [[Liguria]], Trentino Alto Adige, Friuli Venezia Giulia, [[Abruzzo]] and Marche decided to close all schools and universities for two days to a week. Court proceedings were postponed until further notice.<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n\n[[File:Is COVID-19 like a flu? ENG.png|upright=1.13|thumb|Starting from the 9th week of the year, ICU cases related to COVID-19 started to appear in the hospitals. Their spike showed a different behaviour than the cases of seasonal flu.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilgiornale.it/news/cronache/coronavirus-non-affatto-linfluenza-ecco-grafico-che-dimostra-1837298.html|title=Il coronavirus non \u00e8 affatto come l'influenza: ecco il grafico che lo dimostra|publisher=[[Il Giornale]]|language=it|access-date=2020-03-17 |first=Federico |last=Giuliani}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https: