ualni-data_18455_4122_1.html|title=COVID-19: aktu\u00e1ln\u00ed data|website=DR|language=cs|access-date=2020-03-02}}</ref> As of 8 March 24 of 31 confirmed cases in the country have links to Italy, leading the government to institute a mandatory quarantine for all persons with a history of recent travel to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/koronavirus-nemocnice-bulovka-pocet-potvrzenych-pripadu.A200308_124539_domaci_remy|title=Koronavirus: 32 p\u0159\u00edpad\u016f, kontroly na hranic\u00edch i omezen\u00ed v domovech senior\u016f|date=8 March 2020|website=iDNES.cz|accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Denmark]]''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, Denmark confirmed its first case, a man who had returned from a ski holiday in [[Valmalenco]], [[Sondrio]] and was tested at [[Zealand University Hospital, Roskilde]] and quarantined at home.<ref name=Braagaard2020>{{cite news | last=Braagaard | first=Natali | date=27 February 2020 | title=Dansker smittet med coronavirus | url=https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-02-27-dansker-smittet-med-coronavirus | publisher=[[TV 2 (Denmark)|TV2 News]] | language=Danish | trans-title=Dane infected with coronavirus | accessdate=27 February 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/indland/foerste-dansker-smittet-med-coronavirus-vi-er-selvfoelgelig-dybt-rystede|title=F\u00f8rste dansker smittet med coronavirus: 'Vi er selvf\u00f8lgelig dybt rystede'|website=DR|language=da-DK|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a man who had returned from a ski holiday in Northern Italy on 15 February tested positive at [[Rigshospitalet]] in Copenhagen and was placed in home quarantine.<ref name=\"sst28February\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sst.dk/da/Nyheder/2020/En-person-der-er-blevet-undersoegt-paa-Rigshospitalet-er-det-andet-bekraeftede-tilfaelde-af-COVID-19|title=En person, der er blevet unders\u00f8gt p\u00e5 Rigshospitalet, er det andet bekr\u00e6ftede tilf\u00e6lde af COVID-19 i Danmark|date=28 February 2020|work=Sundhedsstyrelsen (Danish Health Authority)|language=da|trans-title=A person, that has been tested at Rigshospitalet, is the second confirmed case of COVID-19 in Denmark|url-status=live|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 29 February, an employee at the [[Aarhus University Hospital]] who had been to a conference in Munich, Germany, where he had met an infected person from Italy, tested positive.<ref name=Ingvorsen2020>{{cite news | last=Ingvorsen | first=Emil S\u00f8nderg\u00e5rd | date=29 February 2020 | title=Nyt coronatilf\u00e6lde er en medarbejder p\u00e5 Aarhus Universitetshospital | url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/indland/nyt-coronatilfaelde-er-en-medarbejder-paa-aarhus-universitetshospital | publisher=[[DR (broadcaster)|DR]] | language=Danish | trans-title=New corona case is a worker at Aahus university hospital | accessdate=29 February 2020 }}</ref> On 3 March, five people who had returned from Northern Italy tested positive.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Andreasen|first=Kasper B.|url=https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-03-03-femte-og-sjette-dansker-smittet-med-coronavirus|title=Femte og sjette dansker smittet med coronavirus|date=3 March 2020|work=TV 2|access-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live|language=da}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Hagemann-Nielsen|first=Frederik|url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/indland/sundhedsminister-mindst-10-herhjemme-er-nu-smittet-med-corona|title=Sundhedsminister: Mindst 10 herhjemme er nu smittet med corona|date=3 March 2020|work=DR|access-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live|language=da}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Estonia]]''' \u2013\nOn 3 March, Estonia confirmed its second case, a patient who had arrived on 29 February from Bergamo and was travelling through [[Riga Airport]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Second case of coronavirus diagnosed in Estonia |url=https://news.err.ee/1059432/second-case-of-coronavirus-diagnosed-in-estonia |publisher=ERR |accessdate=4 March 2020|date=3 March 2020 }}</ref> Two other Estonian passengers from the same flight and one returnee from Bergamo arriving through Tallinn Airport tested positive on 5 March.<ref>{{cite web |title=Third coronavirus case confirmed in Estonia |url=https://news.err.ee/1059950/third-coronavirus-case-confirmed-in-estonia |publisher=ERR |accessdate=5 March 2020|date=5 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Kahel Bergamost naasnud tallinlasel tuvastati koroonaviirus |url=https://www.err.ee/1060498/kahel-bergamost-naasnud-tallinlasel-tuvastati-koroonaviirus |publisher=ERR |accessdate=5 March 2020 |language=Estonian| trans-title=Two Tallinners returning from Bergamo infected with coronavirus|date=5 March 2020 }}</ref> Two cases in [[Saaremaa]] were confirmed on 10 March: the patients had been in contact with the [[Power Volley Milano]] team members during the [[2019\u201320 CEV Challenge Cup]] matches held in Saaremaa on 4 and 5 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lisandus veel kolm koroonasse nakatunut |language=Estonian |trans-title=Three new corona cases |url= https://www.err.ee/1062388/lisandus-veel-kolm-koroonasse-nakatunut |publisher=ERR |accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=17th person diagnosed with coronavirus in Estonia |url=https://news.err.ee/1062618/17th-person-diagnosed-with-coronavirus-in-estonia |publisher=ERR |accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref> On 9 March 5 Milan players had been diagnosed with fever before a league match.<ref>{{cite news |title=Volley, febbre al termoscanner: Milano-Padova non si gioca |language=Italian |trans-title=Volleyball, thermoscanner fever: Milan-Padua is not played |url=https://sport.sky.it/volley/2020/03/08/coronavirus-volley-partita-sospesa-milano-padova |publisher=Sky Sport |accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref> The infected in Saaremaa included the CEO of the [[Saaremaa VK]] volleyball club.<ref>{{cite news |title=Koroonaviiruse saanud Saaremaa v\u00f5rkpallimeeskonna juht: loodan, et see olukord laheneb v\u00f5imalikult kiiresti |language=Estonian |trans-title=Infected head of Saaremaa volleyball t